  "plainText": "Don't Starve\nTogether\nElectrical Doodad\n\"Science away! Bzzzt!\"\nObject Info\n10\nSource\nDropped by\n:\n:\nCrafting\nWagstaffNormal (RoG)\n×2 ×1 ( only)\nTab\nTier\nAlways available\n×2 ×1\nTab\nTier\nMiscellaneous\n\"transistor\"\n“It's whirring with electricity.”\n–Wilson\n“Electrical doo-dah, doo-dah.”\n–Willow\n“Science bean.”\n–Wolfgang\n“Electrical doo-what?”\n–Wendy\n“GREETINGS, SISTER”\n–WX-78\n“This is quite advanced technology.”\n–Wickerbottom\n“I won't even pretend to know how that works.”\n–Woodie\n“I don't understand how it works, but it does.”\n–Maxwell\n“A crystal diode made of gold and rocks! I have many uses for this!”\n–Wagstaff\n“A marvel öf science.”\n–Wigfrid\n“We are getting good at crafting!”\n–Webber\n“Thing-y that does the science stuff!”\n–Walani\n“Positively charged to get my hands on one!”\n–Warly\n“Whut be this?”\n–Woodlegs\n“ALL THAT GLITTERS IS'T GOLD?”\n–Wilba\n“It's humming! Hummm...”\n–Wormwood\n“One of these is nice. Two is better.”\n–Wheeler\n“A thing of beauty.”\n–Winona\n“I do not know what this does.”\n–Wortox\n“It buzzing! Bees stuck inside?”\n–Wurt\n“Of course I know what it is! It's uh... um...”\n–Walter\n“Is this one of those newfangled electric thinga-ma-whoosits?”\n–Wanda\nThe Electrical Doodad is a Tinkering Tab Item exclusive to Wagstaff. It costs 1 Cut Stone and 2 Gold Nuggets to craft. It can be used to craft the Infroggles, the Telebrella and the Telipad.\nIn DLCs and Don't Starve Together, the Electrical Doodad can be crafted by all Characters. It is found in the Science Tab and requires a Science Machine to prototype. It is used in several more recipes, such as the Alchemy Engine, Endothermic Fire Pit, and Ice Flingomatic.\nIn Reign of Giants DLC, Electrical Doodads have a small chance to be coughed up by friendly Catcoons.\nIn Shipwrecked DLC, Electrical Doodads also have a small chance to be found in X Marks the Spot treasure chests.\nUsage[edit | edit source]\n×2\n×2\n×2\n×4\n×10\n×2\n×2\n×4\n×2\n×15\n×2\n×3\n×3\n×2\n×4\n×2\n×2\n×2\n×2\n×2\n×2\n×2\n×4\n×2\n×5\n×2\n×2\n×2\n×2\nTrivia[edit | edit source]\nElectrical Doodads were first introduced in the Reign of Giants DLC. During the Early Access phase of the Hamlet DLC, they were then retroactively added to the base game to allow Wagstaff to craft his specific items.\nElectrical Doodads used to be crafted from the Refine Tab.\nElectrical Doodads were initially added to make it harder to craft crucial objects, like the Alchemy Engine.\nPer Wagstaff's quote as well as its appearance, the Electrical Doodad is a diode despite its spawn code referring to it as a transistor.\nDSTDSRoGSWHam\nView or edit this template\nDon't Starve Together Craftable Items\nRegular Filters\nSurvivor Items\nWilson\nWillow\nWolfgang\nWendy\nWX-78\nWickerbottom\nWoodie\nWes\nMaxwell\nWigfrid\nWebber\nWarly\nWortox\nWormwood\nWinona\nWurt\nWalter\nWanda\nTools\nLight Sources\nPrototypers & Stations\nRefined Materials\nWeapons\nArmor\nClothing\nHealing\nMagic\nDecorations\nStructures\nStorage Solutions\nCooking\nFood & Gardening\nFishing\nSeafaring\nBeefalo Riding\nWinter Items\nSummer Items\nRain Gear\nCrafting Station Filters\nSpecial Event\nAncient Pseudoscience\nCarpentry\nCartography\nCritters\nCelestial\nBrightsmithy\nShadowcraft\nFabrication\nBottle Exchange\nCombrining Filter\nTea Brewing Filter\nSculptures\nSeasonings\nTrading\nTrading Hutch\nOfferings\nCawnival Creation\nTrinket Trove\nMad Science\nWinter's Feast Cooking\nSanctum Smithy Filter\nCustom Course Shack Filter\nView or edit this template\nDon't Starve Craftable Items\nTools\nLight\nSurvival\nFood\nScience\nFight\nStructures\nRefine\nMagic\nDress\nAncient\nBooks\nTinkering\nView or edit this template\nDon't Starve: Reign of Giants Craftable Items\nTools\nLight\nSurvival\nFood\nScience\nFight\nStructures\nRefine\nMagic\nDress\nAncient\nBooks\nTinkering\nView or edit this template\nDon't Starve Shipwrecked and Volcano Craftable Items\nTools\nLight\nNautical\nSurvival\nFood\nScience\nFight\nStructures\nRefine\nMagic\nDress\nVolcanic\nBooks\nTinkering\nView or edit this template\nDon't Starve Hamlet Craftable Items\nTools\nLight\nTreasure Hunting\nSurvival\nNautical\nFood\nScience\nFight\nStructures\nRefine\nMagic\nDress\nGreen Thumb\nBooks\nTinkering\nCity Planning\nRenovate\nFloors\nShelves\nPlantholders\nColumns\nWall Papers\nHanging Lamps\nOrnaments\nChairs\nHome Kits\nDoors\nWindows\nRugs\nLamps\nTables",
