  "wikitext": "{{Navbutton/Separation}}\n{{Object Infobox\n|image=Electrical Doodad Dropped.png\n|icon=Electrical Doodad.png\n|stack       = 10\n|spawnCode   = \"transistor\"\n|description = Science away! Bzzzt!\n|crafting_infobox = \n<tabber>\nWagstaff=\n{{Craft Infobox\n|ingredient1 = Gold Nugget\n|multiplier1 = 2\n|ingredient2 = Cut Stone\n|multiplier2 = 1 ({{Pic|28|Wagstaff Portrait|Wagstaff}} only)\n|tab         = Tinkering\n|tier        = 0\n}}\n|-|\nNormal (RoG)=\n{{Craft Infobox\n|ingredient1 = Gold Nugget\n|multiplier1 = 2\n|ingredient2 = Cut Stone\n|multiplier2 = 1 {{RoG}}\n|tab         = Science\n|tier        = 1\n}}\n</tabber>\n|droppedBy = {{Pic24|Reign of Giants icon}}: {{Pic32|Catcoon}}<hr>{{Pic24|Shipwrecked icon}}: {{Pic|20|Slotmachine}} {{Pic32|X Marks The Spot}}\n}}\n\n{{Quotes\n|wilson = It's whirring with electricity.\n|willow = Electrical doo-dah, doo-dah.\n|wolfgang = Science bean.\n|wendy = Electrical doo-what?\n|wx78 = GREETINGS, SISTER\n|wickerbottom = This is quite advanced technology.\n|woodie = I won't even pretend to know how that works.\n|maxwell = I don't understand how it works, but it does.\n|wagstaff = A crystal diode made of gold and rocks! I have many uses for this!\n|wigfrid = A marvel öf science.\n|webber = We are getting good at crafting!\n|walani = Thing-y that does the science stuff!\n|warly = Positively charged to get my hands on one!\n|woodlegs = Whut be this?\n|wilba = ALL THAT GLITTERS IS'T GOLD?\n|wormwood = It's humming! Hummm...\n|wheeler = One of these is nice. Two is better.\n|winona = A thing of beauty.\n|wortox = I do not know what this does.\n|wurt = It buzzing! Bees stuck inside?\n|walter = Of course I know what it is! It's uh... um...\n|wanda = Is this one of those newfangled electric thinga-ma-whoosits?\n|choose = wagstaff\n}}\n\nThe '''Electrical Doodad''' is a [[Tinkering Tab]] [[Item]] exclusive to [[Wagstaff]]. It costs 1 [[Cut Stone]] and 2 [[Gold Nugget]]s to craft. It can be used to craft the [[Infroggles]], the [[Telebrella]] and the [[Telipad]].\n\nIn [[DLC]]s and ''[[Don't Starve Together]]'', the Electrical Doodad can be crafted by all [[Characters]]. It is found in the [[Science Tab]] and requires a [[Science Machine]] to prototype. It is used in several more recipes, such as the [[Alchemy Engine]], [[Endothermic Fire#Endothermic Fire Pit|Endothermic Fire Pit]], and [[Ice Flingomatic]].\n\nIn ''[[Don't Starve: Reign of Giants|Reign of Giants]]'' DLC, Electrical Doodads have a small chance to be coughed up by friendly [[Catcoon]]s.\n\nIn ''[[Don't Starve: Shipwrecked|Shipwrecked]]'' DLC, Electrical Doodads also have a small chance to be found in [[X Marks the Spot]] treasure chests.\n\n{{Clear}}\n\n=={{pic|32|Icon Tools}} Usage==\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Electrical Doodad\n|item2 = Spectoggles\n|item3 = Torch\n|count3 = 2\n|result = Infroggles\n|character = Wagstaff}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Electrical Doodad\n|item2 = Pretty Parasol\n|result = Telebrella\n|character = Wagstaff}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Electrical Doodad\n|item2 = Gears\n|item3 = Cut Stone\n|count3 = 2\n|result = Telipad\n|character = Wagstaff}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Electrical Doodad\n|count1 = 2\n|item2 = Rope\n|count2 = 4\n|item3 = Ice\n|count3 = 10\n|tool = Alchemy Engine\n|result = Ice Cube\n|dlc = Reign of Giants}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Electrical Doodad\n|count1 = 2\n|item2 = Cut Stone\n|count2 = 2\n|item3 = Boards\n|count3 = 4\n|tool = Science Machine\n|result = Alchemy Engine\n|dlc = Reign of Giants}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Electrical Doodad\n|count1 = 2\n|item2 = Ice\n|count2 = 15\n|item3 = Gears\n|count3 = 2\n|tool = Alchemy Engine\n|result = Ice Flingomatic\n|dlc = Reign of Giants}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Electrical Doodad\n|count1 = 3\n|item2 = Gears\n|count2 = 3\n|item3 = Thick Fur\n|tool = Alchemy Engine\n|result = Insulated Pack\n|dlc = Reign of Giants}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Electrical Doodad\n|count1 = 1\n|item2 = Gears\n|count2 = 1\n|item3 = Thick Fur\n|tool = Alchemy Engine\n|result = Insulated Pack\n|dlc = DST}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Electrical Doodad\n|count1 = 2\n|item2 = Cut Stone\n|count2 = 4\n|item3 = Nitre\n|count3 = 2\n|tool = Alchemy Engine\n|result = Endothermic Fire Pit\n|dlc = Reign of Giants}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Electrical Doodad\n|count1 = 2\n|item2 = Moleworm\n|count2 = 2\n|item3 = Glow Berry\n|tool = Alchemy Engine\n|result = Moggles\n|dlc = Reign of Giants}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Electrical Doodad\n|count1 = 2\n|item2 = Volt Goat Horn\n|item3 = Nitre\n|count3 = 2\n|tool = Alchemy Engine\n|result = Morning Star\n|dlc = Reign of Giants}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Electrical Doodad\n|count1 = 2\n|item2 = Sand\n|count2 = 2\n|item3 = Limestone\n|count3 = 4\n|tool = Science Machine\n|result = Sea Lab\n|dlc = Shipwrecked}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Electrical Doodad\n|count1 = 2\n|item2 = Thermal Stone\n|item3 = Bamboo\n|count3 = 5\n|tool = Alchemy Engine\n|result = Ice Maker 3000\n|dlc = Shipwrecked}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Electrical Doodad\n|count1 = 2\n|item2 = Quacken Beak\n|item3 = Gears\n|tool = Alchemy Engine\n|result = Quacken Drill\n|dlc = Shipwrecked}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Electrical Doodad\n|item2 = Turbine Blades\n|item3 = Gold Nugget\n|count3 = 2\n|tool = Alchemy Engine\n|result = Iron Wind\n|dlc = Shipwrecked}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Electrical Doodad\n|count1 = 2\n|item2 = Alloy\n|count2 = 2\n|item3 = Gears\n|tool = Alchemy Engine\n|result = Oscillating Fan\n|dlc = Hamlet}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Electrical Doodad\n|item2 = Alloy\n|item3 = Lantern\n|tool = Key to the City\n|result = Lamp Post\n|dlc = Hamlet}}\n\n== {{pic|32|Placeholder}} Trivia ==\n* Electrical Doodads were first introduced in the ''Reign of Giants'' DLC. During the Early Access phase of the ''[[Don't Starve: Hamlet|Hamlet]]'' DLC, they were then retroactively added to the base game to allow Wagstaff to craft his specific items.\n* Electrical Doodads used to be crafted from the [[Refine Tab]].\n* Electrical Doodads were initially added to make it harder to craft crucial objects, like the Alchemy Engine.\n* Per Wagstaff's quote as well as its appearance, the Electrical Doodad is a diode despite its spawn code referring to it as a transistor.\n\n{{Craftable Items}}\n[[Category:Craftable Items]]\n[[Category:Science Tab]]\n[[Category:Tinkering Tab]]\n[[Category:Items]]\n[[Category:Mob Dropped Items]]\n[[Category:Science]]\n[[Category:Non-Flammable]]\n[[zh:电子元件]]\n[[es:Artilugio eléctrico]]\n[[vi:Doodad Điện]]"
}
